Description: iArt (Imputation-Assisted Randomization Tests) is an R package designed for conducting finite-population-exact randomization tests in design-based causal studies with missing outcomes. It provides a robust solution for handling missing data in causal inference, leveraging the potential outcomes framework and integrating various outcome imputation algorithms.
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
